-- Wells Fargo Lending Discrimination Case Seen Possible by U.S.
-- B y   S e t h   S t e r n
-- 2012-05-31T18:42:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-31/wells-fargo-lending-discrimination-case-seen-possible-by-u-s-.html
The  Justice Department  has
“sufficient basis” to file a lending discrimination complaint
against Wells Fargo & Co., the largest U.S. mortgage lender,
said Assistant Attorney General Thomas Perez in a conference
call with reporters today.  Wells Fargo previously disclosed a probe into the matter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Seth Stern in Washington at 
